    <svcsubproc id="hl1603002">
        <title>Heater Core And Evaporator Core Housing</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Anytime the refrigerant system is opened, the lubricant in the system must be replaced after the
                    system is reassembled. The amount of lubricant, and the method of adding it to the system, varies
                    based on the service performed on the system. To determine the correct amount of lubricant
                    (refrigerant oil), refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603007.xml" xrefid="hl1603007">OIL FILL GUIDELINES</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Anytime an A/C fitting is disconnected, the O-ring must be replaced. The new O-ring must be
                    lubricated with mineral-based oil (International P/N ZGGR725008). Never use grease, penetrating oil,
                    motor oil, ester or PAG oil, etc. to lubricate O-rings and fittings.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Installation of a new receiver/drier is not required when repairing the air conditioning system,
                    except:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>when there is physical evidence of system contamination from a failed A/C compressor;
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>when there is damage to the receiver/drier;</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>or, when the quantity of refrigerant oil retained in the system cannot otherwise be
                            accurately determined.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the radiator grille.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recover the refrigerant. For additional information, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603003.xml" xrefid="hl1603003">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM (REFRIGERANT
                    RECOVERY)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain the engine cooling system. For additional information, refer to the EGES 305, ENGINE
                DIAGNOSTICS MANUAL.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the instrument panel (refer to S16032).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the clamps and disconnect the heater hoses at the heater core.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020496.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 14.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the evaporator inlet and outlet lines. Cap all openings until ready to
                re-install.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Discard the O-ring seals.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To install, tighten the evaporator inlet line fitting to 23 Nm (17 lbf-ft).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To install, tighten the evaporator outlet line fitting to 66 Nm (49 lbf-ft).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201011" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020497.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Disconnect the evaporator inlet line fitting.</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Disconnect the evaporator outlet line fitting.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the heater core and evaporator core housing electrical connectors.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201012" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020498.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 15.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector and detach the wire harness pin-type retainer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201013" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020499.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 16.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the nuts and position the junction box aside.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201014" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020500.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 17.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the blower motor electrical connector.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201015" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020501.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 18.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the support brace (Figure 23).</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten the support brace retainers to 42 Nm (31 lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201016" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020502.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Remove the ground nut.</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Remove the 2 support brace retainers.</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Remove the support brace.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2 heater core and evaporator core housing nuts and 3 heater core and evaporator
                core housing bolts.
            </para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten the support brace retainers to 6 Nm (53 lbf-in).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201017" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020503.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 19.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the heater core and evaporator core housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Install new O-ring seals.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill the engine cooling system. For additional information, refer to the EGES 305, ENGINE
                DIAGNOSTICS MANUAL.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Evacuate, leak test and charge the refrigerant system. For additional information, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603005.xml" xrefid="hl1603005">EVACUATING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
